					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">No, it's not. It should be <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">&#40;a / 0x100&#41; != &#40;b / 0x100&#41;</tt>, or <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">&#40;a &gt;&gt; 8&#41; != &#40;b &gt;&gt; 8&#41;</tt>, or <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">&#40;a &amp; 0xFF00&#41; != &#40;b &amp; 0xFF00&#41;</tt>. Essentially you should be extracting the high 8 bits (= the page) from the addresses and comparing them.</div>

					
