					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">amhndu wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">If I understand  you correctly, only the PPU, APU and mapper registers need to touched in the proper cycle, the CPU registers. the ROM and the SRAM read-writes are malleable ?</div><br />Correct, with the proviso that some mappers &quot;snoop&quot; RAM writes by placing mapper registers at the same address as certain parts of RAM. This includes a few MMC1/MMC3 multicart mappers' outer bank registers as well as the bank registers in the NINA half of mapper 34. But so far, all such &quot;snooping&quot; that I'm aware of is not cycle sensitive.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">amhndu wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I should say that I'm not really aiming for perfect emulation and 100% game coverage.</div><br />So in other words, are you saying your project is type &quot;a&quot; (early stage) in <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?p=30784#p30784" class="postlink">this taxonomy</a>?</div>

